Deterministic validator behavior

Immutable authorship lineage

Predictable constitutional logic

Zero doctrinal drift

Audit‑ready transparency

These requirements apply to every repository, module, document, and governance artifact.

1. Structural Hierarchy Requirements
Every repository must follow the SAIA‑Class S hierarchical structure, consisting of:

Root Authority Layer — constitutional, doctrinal, federal‑record artifacts

Core Engine Layer — identity, registry, predictive, harm‑prevention logic

Governance Layer — policies, procedures, validators, workflows

Operational Layer — modules, services, interfaces

Documentation Layer — READMEs, governance docs, audit manifests

Public Layer — non‑sensitive, non‑federal‑record materials

No artifact may be placed outside its designated layer.

